	painsBodyHtml={`<p>Behind every statistic is a real student — maybe you. The endless scroll that leaves you feeling behind. The grade that somehow became a verdict on your worth. The future everyone keeps asking about when you're just trying to get through today. The version of yourself you perform online while the real you feels unseen.</p><p>None of this means something is wrong with you. It means you're human, living in a world that ties your value to your performance and your popularity — and that's a weight no one was built to carry. There is a Father who sees the real you underneath all of it, and He has something to say about who you actually are.</p>`}
