		{ ref: `Jeremiah 29:11`, slug: `jeremiah`, ch: 29, text: `For I know the plans I have for you, declares your Father — plans for your welfare and not for harm, to give you a future and a hope.`, note: `When the future feels like a question mark, your Father already has plans for it — good ones.` },
		{ ref: `Philippians 4:6-7`, slug: `philippians`, ch: 4, text: `Do not be anxious about anything, but in everything, by prayer, bring your requests to your Father — and His peace, beyond all understanding, will guard your heart and mind.`, note: `You don't have to white-knuckle the anxiety alone — hand it to your Father and let His peace stand guard.` },
		{ ref: `Romans 8:38-39`, slug: `romans`, ch: 8, text: `Nothing — not failure, not the future, not anything in all creation — can separate you from the love of your Father.`, note: `No bad grade, no breakup, no mistake can cut you off from His love. Nothing.` },
		{ ref: `John 1:12`, slug: `john`, ch: 1, text: `But to all who received Him, who believed in His name, He gave the right to become children of your Father.`, note: `Being His child isn't something you earn — it's a gift you receive.` },
		{ ref: `1 Samuel 16:7`, slug: `1-samuel`, ch: 16, text: `Your Father does not see as people see; people look at the outward appearance, but your Father looks at the heart.`, note: `The world judges your surface — your Father sees the real you, and loves what He sees.` },
