	voices={[
		{ quote: `There is heaven in the depth of that word — Father.`, name: `Charles Spurgeon`, role: `the “Prince of Preachers”`, photo: `https://cdn.sanity.io/images/rusi1hyi/production/e48a128da123135241be9c95cf35b37498d94ea5-500x617.jpg` },
		{ quote: `The hardest, gladdest thing in the world is, to cry Father! from a full heart.`, name: `George MacDonald`, role: `who taught that the Fatherhood of God is the heart of the gospel`, photo: `https://cdn.sanity.io/images/rusi1hyi/production/35e71c2610893383d20b60883aa0b1d4d4664cbc-500x726.jpg` },
		{ quote: `Answered prayer is the interchange of love between the Father and His child.`, name: `Andrew Murray`, role: `who taught a generation to live as the Father's children`, photo: `https://cdn.sanity.io/images/rusi1hyi/production/133bc45cfa954cf1ae99b7afac5954eca764ed70-500x830.jpg` },
	]}
	voicesCreditHtml={`Photos via <a href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">Wikimedia Commons</a> &mdash; Charles Spurgeon, George MacDonald, and Andrew Murray (all public domain).`}
	wordHeading={`His Word will not return void`}
	wordBodyHtml={`<p>You might not feel different the first time you read it. That's okay. The Father's love isn't a hype feeling — it's a foundation, and foundations get built quietly, one day at a time. Every verse you take in is your Father planting something in you that the pressure can't uproot.</p><p class="mt-4" style="color: var(--color-ink);">"My word… will not return to me empty, but will accomplish that which I purpose." <span style="color: var(--color-muted);">— Isaiah 55:11</span></p>`}
	fatherSaysHeading={`What your Father says over you`}
	fatherSaysHtml={`<p>"I know the pressure you're under. I see the grade you're stressing about, the message you keep re-reading, the future that feels too big. And I want you to hear Me over all of it: you are Mine, and I love you right now — not the future you, not the fixed-up you. You.</p><p>You don't have to earn My love with good grades or impress Me to keep it. I made you on purpose, and I called you wonderful before you did a single thing. When you feel like you're not enough, come to Me — I'll quiet you with My love and remind you who you really are. You don't have to perform for Me. You just have to come. I'm your Father, I delight in you, and nothing in this world can change that."</p>`}
	prayerHeading={`A prayer for high schoolers`}
	prayerHtml={`<p>Our Father, we thank You and praise You for these high schoolers — every student carrying more than anyone sees. Let them hear Your whisper above their noise — the comparison, the pressure, the voices online that never go quiet. Let them encounter Your love — not as a rule, but as a Father's delight — and know they are Your beloved, apart from their grades, their follows, or their looks.</p><p>Give them grace to receive their identity from You before the world tells them who to be. Father, steady them in the anxiety, give them friends who point them to You, and carry them through the late nights and the hard days when they feel like they're not enough. I pray Your protection over them from the enemy, from temptation, from the pull of comparison and the lie that they have to perform to be loved, and from despair.</p><p>Let them know there is no condemnation in You, that they are fearfully and wonderfully made, and that nothing can separate them from Your love. Let them know You, their Father, as their true home and reward. And may they wake up every single day knowing they are loved by their heavenly Father.</p><p>In Jesus' name, amen.</p>`}
