	faqs={[
		{ question: `What are good Bible verses for high schoolers?`, answer: `Psalm 139:14 (fearfully and wonderfully made), Jeremiah 29:11 (plans for a future and a hope), Philippians 4:6-7 (do not be anxious), Romans 8:38-39 (nothing can separate you from God's love), John 1:12 (you can become a child of God), Isaiah 43:1 (I have called you by name, you are Mine), and Zephaniah 3:17 (He rejoices over you) all speak straight to what high schoolers carry. Read and hear them free in the Father's Heart Bible™ at fathersheartbible.com/read.` },
		{ question: `What does the Bible say about anxiety and pressure in high school?`, answer: `Scripture takes your anxiety seriously and offers a real place to put it. Philippians 4:6-7 says don't be anxious about anything, but bring your requests to God, and His peace will guard your heart and mind. The Father's Heart Bible™ reveals God as a Father you can actually hand the pressure to — read those passages free, with audio, at fathersheartbible.com/read.` },
		{ question: `Does God love me even when my grades or life feel like a mess?`, answer: `Yes — and that's the whole point. Your worth was never your GPA or your performance. Romans 8:38-39 says nothing can separate you from God's love, and 1 Samuel 16:7 says He looks at your heart, not your surface. In the Father's Heart Bible™ you meet God as a Father who delights in you right now, not the fixed-up version you're trying to become.` },
		{ question: `What does the Bible say about comparing myself to others online?`, answer: `The Bible reframes where your worth comes from entirely. 1 Samuel 16:7 says people look at the outward appearance, but God looks at the heart, and Galatians 1:10 invites you to live for God's approval instead of everyone else's. Psalm 139:14 reminds you that you were fearfully and wonderfully made — not a worse version of someone else's highlight reel. Read these free in the Father's Heart Bible™.` },
		{ question: `Is there a free Bible with audio for teens and students?`, answer: `Yes. The Father's Heart Bible™ is free to read and listen to online — no account, no purchase, no app. Open fathersheartbible.com/read on your phone and read or hear any book — perfect for listening on the bus, before a test, or when anxiety hits late at night.` },
		{ question: `What makes the Father's Heart Bible™ different for high schoolers?`, answer: `It's the first English translation to reveal God as Father wherever Scripture reveals Him as Father — so instead of reading one more voice telling you to measure up, you meet the One who already delights in you. For a student under constant pressure to perform, that reframes everything: you come to the Bible as a loved child first, not a project to be graded.` },
		{ question: `How can I start reading the Bible as a high schooler?`, answer: `Start small and start free. Open fathersheartbible.com/read, pick a short book or a Psalm, and listen to the audio while you read. Try a verse a day — Psalm 139, Philippians 4, or Romans 8 are great places to begin. Our how-to-pray guide and verses-by-topic pages can help you find words for whatever you're facing right now.` },
